          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1644330213512-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1644330213512-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1644330213512-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Cut your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>in 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> and stir in your <strong>tomato paste </strong>and <strong>Henderson's Relish </strong>– this is your<strong> tomato stock</strong></p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>cannellini beans</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1644330218536-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1644330218536-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1644330218536-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1644330218536-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1644330218536-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, <strong>hob-safe</strong> <strong>oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Note: Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p><p>Add the <strong>onion wedges</strong>, <strong>tomato wedges</strong>, <strong>drained cannellini beans</strong>, <strong>ground smoked paprika </strong>and <strong>chipotle paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the dish, then add the <strong>tomato stock</strong> and bring to the boil</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1644330226420-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1644330226420-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1644330226420-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1644330226420-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1644330226420-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>BBQ pulled pork</strong> and any juices to the dish<strong> </strong>and give everything a gentle mix up until the pork is covered in the stock</p><p>Put the dish in the oven, uncovered, for 35-40 min or until everything is cooked through and tender</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1644330246644-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
