          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1644330257988-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your<strong> white wine vinegar </strong>with <strong>half </strong>of your <strong>soured cream</strong>, <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>chopped chives </strong>(save the rest for garnish!), a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>in a small bowl – this is your<strong> creamy dressing</strong></p><p>While the BBQ pork is cooking, use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1644330281669-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1644330281669-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1644330281669-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1644330281669-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1644330281669-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once everything is cooked through, remove the casserole dish from the oven and pull the <strong>pork </strong>apart, using two forks (or keep it in bigger chunks if you prefer!) – this is your <strong>smoky pulled pork & beans</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1644330289981-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1644330289981-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1644330289981-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1644330289981-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1644330289981-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut your<strong> jacket potato</strong> in half (careful – it will be hot!), add a knob of <strong>butter</strong>, then load on the <strong>smoky pulled pork & beans</strong></p><p>Top with the <strong>remaining soured cream </strong>and <strong>remaining chopped chives </strong>then season with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Serve the<strong> lettuce wedges</strong> to the side and drizzle over the <strong>creamy dressing</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
